%S A328148 1,3264,168399,2584576,21328125,119952576,518949739,1853620224,
%T A328148 5718836601,15715000000,39312710151,90985918464,197228242549,
%U A328148 404268317376,789541171875,1478257278976,2666742760689,4654606866624,7888229913151,13018560000000
%N A328148 The number of conics tangent to five non-singular curves of degree n in general position, in a projective plane defined over an algebraically closed field of characteristic zero.
%D A328148 William Fulton, Intersection Theory 2nd edition, Springer-Verlag, 1998, page 192.
%H A328148 David Eisenbud and Brady Haran, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NWahomDHaDs">The Journey to 3264</a>, Numberphile video (2023).
%H A328148 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steiner%27s_conic_problem">Steiner's conic problem</a>.
%H A328148 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Enumerative_geometry">Enumerative geometry</a>.
%H A328148 <a href="/index/Rec#order_11">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (11,-55,165,-330,462,-462,330,-165,55,-11,1).
%F A328148 a(n) = n^5 * ((n-1)^5 + 10*(n-1)^4 + 40*(n-1)^3 + 40*(n-1)^2 + 10*(n-1) + 1).
%F A328148 From _Elmo R. Oliveira_, Jun 02 2026: (Start)
%F A328148 G.f.: x*(1 + 3253*x + 132550*x^2 + 911542*x^3 + 1621504*x^4 + 785704*x^5 + 127402*x^6 + 41530*x^7 + 5263*x^8 + 51*x^9) / (1 - x)^11.
%F A328148 E.g.f.: exp(x)*x*(1 + 1631*x + 26435*x^2 + 80440*x^3 + 83805*x^4 + 38102*x^5 + 8440*x^6 + 940*x^7 + 50*x^8 + x^9).
%F A328148 a(n) = 11*a(n-1) - 55*a(n-2) + 165*a(n-3) - 330*a(n-4) + 462*a(n-5) - 462*a(n-6) + 330*a(n-7) - 165*a(n-8) + 55*a(n-9) - 11*a(n-10) + a(n-11). (End)
%e A328148 a(2)=3264 because there are 3264 conics tangent to five conics in general position (Steiner's conic problem).
%K A328148 nonn,easy,changed
%O A328148 1,2
